                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Kingston</placeName>\n                <date>Decr 8th 1857</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I regret I should have so far neg-<lb/>lected my duty to you when I\n                transmitted<lb/> to your care a communication in which I<lb/> was particularly\n                interested, without directly<lb/> addressing you soliciting your kind\n                interference<lb/> &amp; influence, to aid me in the accomplishment<lb/> of my\n                purpose, this would even of itself<lb/> bear the impression, that I was\n                influenced<lb/> by personal motives; but regardless of this,<lb/> permit me to\n                assure you, that there was<lb/> something due on other grounds, viz, my<lb/>\n                personal respect for your position as a teacher<lb/> in\n                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>, and had it not been that I was<lb/> reminded of\n                the fact of my negligence I<lb/> should still have remained the defaulter,<lb/>\n                although quite unintentional; but, repentance<lb/> never comes too late, and will\n                doubtless<lb/> make reparation for my wrong.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have seen your communica-<lb/>tions to <persName>Mr.\n                    Nathan</persName>, by which I am con-<lb/>vinced you have interested yourself in\n                my<lb/> behalf, for which I have to thank you,<lb/> I regret to learn that there has\n                been a division<lb/> in the congregations I should have preferred<lb/> to have heard\n                the “two sticks were united”</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sb3xk0h/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
